<title>267 SOLYMA</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 O PATIENT, spotless One, 
 Our hearts in meekness train
 To bear Thy yoke and learn of Thee, 
 That we may rest obtain.
[V2]
 O Lord, Thou art enough 
 The mind and heart to fill;
 Thy life to calm each anxious thought,
 Thy love each fear dispel.
[V3]
 Oh, fix our earnest gaze
 So wholly, Lord, on Thee
 That, with Thy beauty occupied,
 We elsewhere none may see. Amen.
